SnowSummary: Intermittent Snow - not hard to cross
SnowMentioned: Snow at the beginning; patches of ice
Positive_Negative: Beautiful views

SnowSummary: Snowfields to cross - could be difficult
SnowMentioned: About 50-75% covered in snow/compact ice; snow backdrop
Positive_Negative: Views are great with the snow backdrop; enjoy this one before the road is closed
OtherMentioned: For those in search of fall foliage, the window of opportunity is gone

SnowSummary: Snowfields to cross - could be difficult
SnowMentioned: The shaded sections of the trail were snowy and icy; watch out for ice
Positive_Negative: A nice short hike with great views

SnowSummary: Snowfields to cross - could be difficult
SnowMentioned: Ice on the road starting just past the sunrise turn off
Positive_Negative: Gorgeous day on a great trail
OtherMentioned: Any fall colors are pretty much snow covered

SnowSummary: Intermittent Snow - not hard to cross
SnowMentioned: The shadier side of the loop had some very slick spots with packed ice and snow
Positive_Negative: Absolutely beautiful day on this trail; busy but areas still felt peaceful; this was lovely

SnowSummary: Intermittent Snow - not hard to cross
SnowMentioned: It was pretty icy for the first 1/2 mile or so where the trail is in the shade; muddy spots as well as a little ice
Positive_Negative: Rainier was magnficent; such a nice day
OtherMentioned: The fall color was quite disappointing

SnowSummary: Intermittent Snow - not hard to cross
SnowMentioned: The trail had a few short phases of thin packed ice/snow, especially on the north side
Positive_Negative: Awesome views of Mt Rainier, as advertised!
OtherMentioned: It was not at peak foliage, maybe 1-2 weeks away

SnowSummary: Intermittent Snow - not hard to cross
SnowMentioned: The trip was excellent until the snow came in the afternoon
Positive_Negative: No good view

SnowMentioned: The challenge is that this easy trail sits a top Chinook Pass that will close for the winter once the first heavy snow arrives
Positive_Negative: Favorite short loop hike; trail was damp but in excellent condition; excellent fall hike destination
Would hike this again next year; no bugs and gorgeous views
OtherMentioned: Beautiful fall colors on the whole trail

Positive_Negative: Such a gorgeous day for a hike; excellent views
It was a beautiful day today; trail is in great condition
OtherMentioned: Other fall colors are starting too

Positive_Negative: Beautiful fall evening on the Loop; Rainier was spectacular
Enjoyed our hike on the Loop today; couldn't see Rainier, worth it anyway!
Excellent views despite low clouds and mist; I appreciated the views at the end of the hike much more than the views we started with
An enjoyable day hike; the fast, low moving clouds are just as beautiful as the sunny, mountain views
OtherMentioned: The fall colors are just beginning, should be really great in a week or two

Positive_Negative: The views were amazing; perfect weather except for cloud cover on Rainier
A lovely, easy hike with great views
A bit worried about the weather; spectacular in your face views of Mt Rainier; Not bad for such a popular trail; great day to be out hiking, great weather, great views and an elk sighting to boot
pleasantly surprised with how beautiful and clear the whole trail was; trail was super easy and well maintained; view payout of Rainier was breathtaking
Trail was in good shape, but very busy for the Labor Day weekend

FlowersMentioned: like the wildflowers, which have pretty much petered out at this point
Positive_Negative: Trail is in great shape, no obstacles; enjoyed our supper at the nearly deserted picnic area. What a great evening!
none
The trail was in great shape, and for such a simple trip, you see a ton.
Ground squirrels were the animal of the day. They seemed to be everywhere and adorable as usual.
Notes: This report combined with one about Crystal Mountain Resort

FlowersMentioned: Flowers out but I think we are in transition between full bloom and the beautiful fall foliage.
Positive_Negative:
Beautiful hike even with Mt Rainier playing hide and seek. Can’t wait to go back on a sunny day and see her in all her glory.
Trail was in great condition, somewhat crowded but not bad; Overall great hike on a cooler PNW day.
OtherMentioned: Flowers out but I think we are in transition between full bloom and the beautiful fall foliage.

Positive_Negative: The Naches Loop section of the trail was packed with day hikers, too many kids to count, people feeding wild animals, trampling off trail so overall that section of the trail was pretty annoying for anyone that gets upset when people aren't respecting nature.
Notes: This report combined with one about American Lake

Positive_Negative: I've been looking at doing this trail for a while and I’m so glad I finally did! Even though we had some low clouds throughout the day and didn’t get views of Mt. Rainier, we did get gorgeous views of surrounding mountains.
great hike! awesome views, saw a bear!

I am a novice hiker (for now!) and this hike was spectacular. Coming from Washington's desert (Tri Cities), the mountains and trees and view of Mt. rainier were breathtaking; Great day hike with the family!

FlowersMentioned: Still some lupines but almost gone. Harebells started blooming near Dewey Lake.
Positive_Negative: none
Beautiful day

I love this hike. It is great for most levels of hikers; It was perfect for them and as we rounded the corner at the top of the trail there was Mt. Rainier staring us in the face; It was a great day as all days are near this spectacular mountain.

FlowersMentioned: There are definitely still wildflowers left, but they do appear to be past their peak.
Positive_Negative: What a gorgeous trail! Definitely a summer must-do; Some views were obscured, but even so, those that did show themselves were gorgeous; The trail was fairly busy (expected, given that it was a pleasant Friday) and in great condition.

Found a pretty little spot in the trees with a sandy beach and an amazing view of Rainier - when the clouds lifted:); Rainier lavished us with its beauty all along the way; It was all pretty amazing; Would totally recommend doing the loop from Chinook to Tipsoo; Walking towards Rainier on the other side is astounding; Lots of people on the trail Sunday morning - such beauty draws a crowd.
Notes: This report combined with one about American Lake and one about Dewey Lake

Positive_Negative: I saw so much more on this hike than the previous hike. It was even more beautiful; That was the closest I've ever been to a bear in the wild. It was a magnificent sight; Trail is in great condition

FlowersMentioned: wildflowers still in bloom (but past their prime)
Positive_Negative: Lots of plusses to this hike. The trail is in super condition; plenty of territorial sights that make this hike worth while. Periodic wildlife bonuses of mountain goats and bears (hikers saw two today) add to the adventure.  One of our favorite go to hike due to distance and views.
We had an enjoyable hike that included a bear sighting!

FlowersMentioned: Flowers and butterflies still plentiful in shadier and more moist areas
Positive_Negative: Sun cover is a great idea

FlowersMentioned: The northern flank of the peak has just incredible flowers, even though they look like they are starting to fade already. In some areas they flow over the slopes on the edges of the trail like a waterfall of flower and color.
Positive_Negative: We never got to see the whole peak uncovered but clouds did part in the afternoon leading to some great views.
Notes: This report combined with one about Dewey Lake

FlowersMentioned: The flowers on the north flank are the best I have ever seen. Those on the south side are pretty, but past peak.
Positive_Negative: That said, I had issues with omissions on the WTA description. First, I wish they wouldn't assume all hikers live in Seattle.

FlowersMentioned: Wildflowers are in full bloom at Naches Peak Loop. Starting right from Wooden bridge over Chinook Pass on Pacific Crest trail, we got to see colorful wildflowers; As we passed through the trails, there were sections bloomed with purple lupines, pink and orange paint brush and chamomiles.  The feeling was like we were walking in kingdom of flowers.
Positive_Negative: The unnamed lake was very beautiful with clear waters and surrounding green vegetation.
Great day to hike this trail, sunny but breezy; it is a mild ascent but you will appreciate your views of Mt. Rainier on the descent

FlowersMentioned: Flower power! I've included almost 5min of video highlights below; Wildflowers: our favorite was seeing the uncommon American Speedwell, a coudin to Rainier's famous & common Cusicks Speedwell. Lupine, paintbrush, bistort, valerian, monkeyflower, columbine, larkspur, tiger lily, partridge foot, subalpine daisy, pasqueflower, bear grass, white rhododendron, arnica, groundsel.. and others I've forgotten.
Positive_Negative: What a great family friendly trail to see so many wildflowers right now! Small children will love seeing all the ground squirrels and butterflies
Notes: There is a video too! There are lots of wildflowers in the video although I decided to ignore these for now.

Positive_Negative: Great day hike with The Mountaineers! After the detour is when we got our first views of Rainier, and WOW! Bugs were only bad at the lake, otherwise they were not bothersome. Definitely do this hike! It’s one of my favorites now!
Notes: This report was combined with one for Dewey Lake

Positive_Negative: Wow!

FlowersMentioned: After topping the hill, there is a section through meadows thick with flowers; The flowers on this side of the loop are peak right now, vibrant and full of color; The flowers start getting sparser on the return portion of the loop, probably hotter with less shelter and shade.
Positive_Negative: The bugs started getting annoying here; But the views of Rainier more than make up for it, and you get them the entire walk back; Well worth the drive, even for the short hiking distance

FlowersMentioned: The wild flowers are out in full force right now! Just be respectful and stay on trail. I saw many groups of ppl walking on and through the flowers to take photos.
Positive_Negative: What a beautiful trail! This hike has pay off after pay off; The only downside to going counter clock wise is that you have to remember to turn around to take a look at Naches peak and Mt Rainier. Although, they were out in all their shining glory! There is literally not a bad place to take a photo on this whole hike. Bring sunscreen as there is hardly any tree coverage, and enjoy!

Not terrible considering it was a beautiful summer Sunday in Mt Rainier NP (you just have to expect the crowds at that point). Dewey Lake was totally worth the side trip, and much less populated; Bugs were not bad for me; Beautiful hike and would definitely recommend

FlowersMentioned: Beautiful morning and the wildflowers were out along with great views of Mt Rainier.
Positive_Negative: Maybe not the best decision to take the 10 year old on the steep hike first, but after a little complaining she was in high spirits toward the last part of the hike.We both had fun on a beautiful morning!!

FlowersMentioned: We hiked clockwise as many suggested and were astounded at meadow upon meadow of blooming wildflowers for nearly the entire hike.
Positive_Negative: This is a beautiful and easy hike with amazing views the whole way. Definitely need to return when the berries all along the trail are ripe; This was definitely worth an early morning to beat the crowds.

FlowersMentioned: Beautiful day on the trail, complete with lots of wildflowers and chipmunks.
Positive_Negative: This is an easy hike, without much in the way of elevation gain but spectacular views at all points along the trail; I was glad I arrived and left early.

FlowersMentioned: Wildflower Nirvana! If you want to catch this popular trail at absolute peak wildflower bloom, NOW is the time to go. My wife and I have hiked this trail innumerable times over the years but never caught the wildflowers at quite this peak of perfection before. Lupines galore, Indian paintbrush, beargrass, you name it, it's out there.
Positive_Negative: And now for the bad: massive hordes of people; We did it clockwise and the first hour was not bad with even some moments of solitude. The second half of the hike - Grand Central Station at rush hour, so be warned. Worth it though for the astonishing beauty of the flowers.

FlowersMentioned: Beautiful hike with flowers in full bloom!
Positive_Negative: none
This was a super easy but beautiful hike. Would love to do again and watch the seasons change.
Today we couldn't see the mountain but that was ok; It was a great NW day for a hike!!
The clear skies and peak flower bloom combined to make this just a fabulous hike today - my favorite from among 4 previous times on this trail.

FlowersMentioned: Right now the flowers are amazing, too; If you want to see the flowers, don't hike at night. Everything is washed out in monochrome. We could see hints of purples and reds, that was about it.
Positive_Negative: Naches Peak Loop is a great hike for so many reasons: a loop instead of out-and-back, a little over 3 miles, only 600 feet elevation gain; This trail is fun to hike during a full moon - you can do most of it without your headlamp, and the mountain is often lit up as well. I've also snowshoed this trail in June a few times, that is pretty exciting, too.

First time here, absolutely stunning. Did this clockwise for the best views of the mountain. Had to wait for the morning clouds to burn off but definitely worth the wait. Mosquitoes were annoying so recommend spray or light, long sleeves and pants.
